Hong Kong Stocks Close 1 Percent Higher
HONG KONG , November 19 ( Xinhua ) -- Hong Kong stocks rose about 1 percent Thursday on hopes that local interest rates would ease .
The key Hang Seng Index increased 99.88 points , or 0.98 percent , to close at 10,313.30 after gaining 64.73 points in the previous day 's trade .
The market opened slightly higher at 10,219.88 and hit 10,315.31 at the finish of the morning session .
Buying was focused on rate-sensitive properties and banks , dealers said , with the two sub-indices up 1.55 percent and 1.12 percent respectively .
Dealers said that there was a firm belief that the Hong Kong Association of Bank would announce an interest rate cut after its weekly meeting Friday .
The move would follow the U.S. Federal Reserve 's decision on Tuesday to cut interest rates by 25 basis points , the third rate cut within two months .
The value of turnover fell to 7,141 million HK dollars ( 916 million U.S. dollars ) against the previous day 's 8,400 million HK dollars ( 1,077 million U.S. dollars ) .
